The paper deals with machine learning theory, specifically the development of fast-rate PAC-Bayes bounds. This falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), and data structures (cs.DS) in its analysis.
